rComments: Bumbling ignoramus.  Knows very little (OK, probably nothing) about economics, or other such material closely related to the field.  Explanations are both predictable and tedious:  it seems like he's teaching 7th grade, not a University course.  Looks somewhat confused for the entirity of the lecture, as he reads from his notes.  Devoid of passion.
No preparation for tests. No feedback on essays. Used 40% of class time, which is great if you want to get out of class early, but not great when you're paying $1,000 for a stupid class.
